4️⃣ Hide/Show Menus in Filament

Now we control menu visibility.

Open for example:

app/Filament/Resources/UserResource.php

Add this function:

public static function shouldRegisterNavigation(): bool
{
    $user = auth()->user();

    return \DB::table('role_menu_access')
        ->join('menus', 'menus.id', '=', 'role_menu_access.menu_id')
        ->where('role_menu_access.role_id', $user->role_id)
        ->where('menus.slug', 'users')
        ->exists();
}

What this does:

Check logged user role
↓
Check role_menu_access table
↓
If menu allowed → show
If not allowed → hide
